		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">This project aims to classify an important class of recently discovered so-called c.F4(t)-geometries related to classical and sporadic groups.  At the moment seven examples of flag-transitive c.F4(t)-geometries are known, related to the following groups: Fi22, 3.Fi22, E6(2), 2E6(2), 3.2E6(2), 226.F4(2) and B where the latter is the Baby Monster sporadic simple group.  We have a strong belief that the list is complete and we intend to prove the completeness first under the flag-transitivity assumption.  The final goal is to obtain a purely combinatorial-geometrical characterization of the c.F4(t)-geometries, ie without the initial assumption of any automorphisms of the geometries under consideration.  The combinatorial characterization of the Baby Monster is essentially needed for completion of the classification of all the Petersen-type geometries.  The result can also be used to identify the automorphism group of the vertex operator algebra for the Baby Monster recently constructed by G Hohn.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
